Additional Files: Header for a section where users add additional files to a submission form
Adult: A submission rating. Meaning explicit content or something you wouldn't consider SFW
All Ages: Safe for all ages (found in Pixiv additional options)
Authentication Failed: Message shown when unable to authenticate a website
Bulk: A mode indicator for editing forms in bulk, rather than single (subject to change in the future)
Category: Header for website options that can be put into categories (e.g. FurAffinity)
Charge Patrons: A checkbox option for Patreon (whether to charge patrons or not)
Default Description: Generic description used by all websites unless changed elsewhere
Default Tags: Generic tags used by all websites unless changes elsewhere
Extreme: A submission rating. Refers to adult and anything that could be considered offensive
General: A submission rating. Refers to anything SFW.
In minutes: Denotes that the form field is counted in minutes (1 = 1 minute)
Mature: A submission rating. Refers to things not quite SFW, but not necessarily explicit in nature.
Notify: Common website option. Whether or not to notify watchers (DA, IB, Weasyl)
Schedule: Button text to schedule a submission to post at a certain time
Sexual Content: A checkbox for Pixiv (maybe DA) options that spedcifies if the content has sexual content
Shortcuts: Text for a button that shows description help and shortcuts
Status: FurryNetwork website option to denote status of submission
Title: Title of a submission
Unauthorize: To revoke access to an authorized website (essentially to logout)
Use Title: Tumblr website option to display the title
